{"title_page": "Pajtim Kasami", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| image          = Pajtim Kasami 2016.jpg\n| caption        = Kasami with [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in 2016\n| name           = Pajtim Kasami\n| fullname       = Pajtim Kasami<ref name=\"Barclays Premier League Squad Numbers 2013/14\">{{Cite news\n| title          = Barclays Premier League Squad Numbers 2013/14\n| url            = http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/news/news/2013-14/aug/premier-league-squad-numbers-seasons-2013-14.html\n| publisher      = Premier League\n| date           = 16 August 2013\n| accessdate     = 17 August 2013}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1992|6|2|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Andelfingen, Switzerland]]\n| height         = 1.88m<ref>[http://www.fulhamfc.com/the-teams/first-team/pajtim-kasami Pajtim Kasami | Fulham Football Club<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120827020929/http://www.fulhamfc.com/the-teams/first-team/pajtim-kasami |date=27 August 2012 }}</ref>\n| position       = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub    = [[FC Sion|Sion]]\n| clubnumber     = 13\n| youthyears1    = 2003\u20132006\n| youthclubs1    = [[FC Winterthur|Winterthur]]\n| youthyears2    = 2006\u20132009\n| youthclubs2    = [[Grasshopper Club Z\u00fcrich|Grasshopper]]\n| youthyears3    = 2008\u20132009      | youthclubs3         = \u2192 [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] (loan)\n| youthyears4    = 2009\u20132010      | youthclubs4         = [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]\n| years1         = 2010            | caps1  = 10  | goals1  = 2   | clubs1  = [[AC Bellinzona|Bellinzona]]\n| years2         = 2010\u20132011       | caps2  = 14  | goals2  = 0   | clubs2  = [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]]\n| years3         = 2011\u20132014       | caps3  = 38  | goals3  = 3   | clubs3  = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]\n| years4         = 2012\u20132013       | caps4  = 16  | goals4  = 1   | clubs4  = \u2192 [[FC Luzern|Luzern]] (loan)\n| years5         = 2014\u20132017       | caps5 = 44   | goals5 = 6    | clubs5 = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n| years6         = 2016\u20132017       | caps6 = 25   | goals6 = 2    | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] (loan)\n| years7         = 2017\u20132020       | caps7 = 89   | goals7 = 29    | clubs7 = [[FC Sion|Sion]]\n| nationalyears1 = 2007\u20132008\n| nationalteam1  = [[Switzerland national under-17 football team|Switzerland U17]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 9\n| nationalgoals1 = 3\n| nationalyears2 = 2007\u20132009\n| nationalteam2  = [[Switzerland national under-17 football team|Switzerland U18]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 3\n| nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2010\u20132014\n| nationalteam3  = [[Switzerland national under-21 football team|Switzerland U21]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 31\n| nationalgoals3 = 6\n| nationalyears4 = 2012\n| nationalteam4  = [[Switzerland national under-23 football team|Switzerland U23]]\n| nationalcaps4  = 4\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| nationalyears5 = 2013\u2013\n| nationalteam5  = [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]]\n| nationalcaps5  = 12\n| nationalgoals5 = 2\n| club-update    = 15:13, 25 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 25 March 2020\n}}\n'''Pajtim Kasami''' (born 2 June 1992) is a Swiss [[Association football|footballer]] who last played as a [[midfielder]] for [[FC Sion|Sion]] and the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Le FC Sion s\u2019attache les services de l\u2019international suisse Pajtim Kasami|date=31 August 2017|accessdate=31 August 2017|publisher=www.fcsion.ch|language=French|url=http://fcsion.ch/index.php?r=site/text&id=2073&culture=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/2020/03/20/5e74d472ca474117248b461a.html|title=FC Sion released Alex Song and eight other players for refusing to take pay cuts|access-date=2020-03-25|date=March 20, 2020|language=en|website=www.marca.com}}</ref>\n\n==Early career==\nBorn in [[Z\u00fcrich]], Switzerland<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Olympiakos/kasami_katholoy_aprosmenh_kai_tyxaia_h_nikh_me_atletiko.3037411.html |title=\u039a\u03b1\u03c3\u03ac\u03bc\u03b9: \"\u039d\u03b1 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1\u03c4\u03af \u03b2\u03bf\u03ae\u03b8\u03b7\u03c3\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u039c\u03ae\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03b3\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5\" |publisher=www.sport24.gr |language=Greek}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.enikos.gr/sports/272640,Kasami-Gi-ayto-panhgyrisa-me-ayton-ton-tropo.html |title=\u039a\u03b1\u03c3\u03ac\u03bc\u03b9: \u0393\u03b9\u2019 \u03b1\u03c5\u03c4\u03cc \u03c0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b7\u03b3\u03cd\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03b1\u03c5\u03c4\u03cc\u03bd \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03c4\u03c1\u03cc\u03c0\u03bf| publisher=www.enikos.gr |language=Greek}}</ref> to an [[Albanians|ethnic Albanian]] family from [[Struga]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.zeri.info/futboll/3771/kasami-jam-shqiptar-festova-me-shqiponje-video/ |title=Kasami: Jam shqiptar, festova me shqiponj\u00eb (Video) |publisher=www.zeri.info |language=Albanian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://gazetadita.al/kasami-ja-pse-festova-me-shqiponje/ |title=Kasami: Ja pse festova me shqiponj\u00eb |publisher=gazetadita.al |language=Albanian}}</ref> Kasami started his career in 2003 with Swiss club [[FC Winterthur|Winterthur]] before he joined [[Grasshopper Club Z\u00fcrich|Grasshoppers]] in Z\u00fcrich in 2006. In the same year, he also briefly played for [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] on loan.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/latest-news/youngsters-preparing-for-new-season|title=Youngsters preparing for new season|date=19 August 2008|accessdate=2 February 2014|work=Liverpool FC}}</ref> On 2 February 2009, at age 16, he moved to [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] in the Italian [[Serie A]]. At the start of the 2009\u201310 season, Kasami was reported absent without leave and was due to play for the reserves that season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/ex-liverpool-youngster-kasami-awol-lazio-261824|title=Ex-Liverpool youngster Kasami AWOL from Lazio|date=7 August 2009|accessdate=2 February 2014|work=tribalfootball}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===Bellinzona===\nIn December 2009, Kasami returned to Switzerland to play for [[AC Bellinzona|Bellinzona]], signing a contract until 2011.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://old.acbellinzona.ch/?n=676/pajtim-kasami-e-granata-|title=Pajtim Kasami \u00e8 granata !|date=21 December 2009|accessdate=2 February 2014|publisher=AC Bellinzona|language=Italian}}</ref> He made his professional debut in March after his free transfer was cleared by [[Swiss Football Association]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport.sf.tv/Nachrichten/Archiv/2009/12/21/Fussball/Weltmeister-Pajtim-Kasami-wechselt-zur-AC-Bellinzona|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120911161829/http://www.sport.sf.tv/Nachrichten/Archiv/2009/12/21/Fussball/Weltmeister-Pajtim-Kasami-wechselt-zur-AC-Bellinzona|archivedate=11 September 2012|title=Weltmeister Pajtim Kasami wechselt zur AC Bellinzona|date=7 June 2010|work=Sport SF|language=German|url-status=dead}}</ref> Lazio terminated his contract after Kasami failed to appear on several training sessions in the youth teams or first team, and it was due to his indiscipline that Lazio did not want to sell buy his rights from Grasshopper.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/europa/bellinzona-ag-kasami-contratto-con-la-lazio-rescisso-correttamente-185778|title=Bellinzona, ag. Kasami \"Contratto con la Lazio rescisso correttamente\"|date=30 December 2009|accessdate=2 February 2014|work=Tutto Mercato Web|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\n===Palermo===\nOn 7 June 2010 Palermo announced they had signed the midfielder in a 5-year contract from Bellinzona.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://palermocalcio.it/it/0910/news/scheda.php?id=20914 |publisher=US Citt\u00e0 di Palermo |language=Italian |date=7 June 2010 |accessdate=2 February 2014 |title=PRESO PAJTIM KASAMI}}</ref> Despite his young age, he was immediately included in the first team and made his debut with a ''rosanero'' jersey as a second-half substitute in the first leg of the [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League]] [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|play-off]] against [[NK Maribor|Maribor]]. He then made his Serie A debut later on 30 August, playing the entire home league game against [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]], which ended in a 0\u20130 draw. He concluded the season with 24 appearances: 14 in the [[Serie A|league]], 8 in [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] and 2 in [[Coppa Italia]].<ref name=sw>{{cite web | url = https://int.soccerway.com/players/pajtim-kasami/102652 | title = Switzerland \u2013 P. Kasami \u2013 Soccerway | publisher = Global Sports Media | accessdate = 12 January 2012}}</ref> Zamparini hailed Kasami as \"the new [[Javier Pastore|Pastore]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegrafi.com/zamparini-pajtim-kasami-ai-eshte-pastore-i-ri/|title=Zamparini: Pajtim Kasami? Ai \u00ebsht\u00eb Pastore i ri|publisher=Telegrafi|language=Albanian}}</ref>\n\n===Fulham===\nOn 25 July 2011 Kasami signed for [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] on a four-year deal for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/july/25/pajtim-kasami-joins-fulham | title = Pajtim Kasami Joins Fulham | publisher = Fulham FC | accessdate = 25 July 2011}}</ref> Pajtim Kasami made his d\u00e9but for Fulham as a late substitute in the 0\u20130 draw in their [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] clash with [[RNK Split]]. He was later in the starting line-up versus [[FC Dnipro Dnipropetrovsk|Dnipro]] on 18 August 2011, playing for 88 minutes and was greatly involved in the set up of all the 3 goals.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2012/matches/round=2000271/match=2007220/postmatch/index.html | title = UEFA Europa League 2012 \u2013 Fulham v Dnipro |publisher = UEFA | accessdate = 18 August 2011}}</ref> Kasami made his [[Premier League]] d\u00e9but on 21 August 2011 against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] at the [[Molineux Stadium]]. Fulham lost the match 2\u20130.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.fulhamfc.com/match-centre/2011_2012/league/away/wolverhampton-wanderers | title = Wolves 2 \u2013 0 Fulham | publisher = Fulham FC | accessdate = 2 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nKasami almost joined Pescara on loan on 1 January 2013, but the move could not be finalised in time due to a bad internet connection.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2013/01/31/pajtim-kasamis-loan-move-to-pescara-collapses-over-dodgy-internet-connection-3377081/|title=Kasami's Pescara Loan|publisher=Metro UK|accessdate=17 May 2014}}</ref> Kasami joined [[FC Luzern|Luzern]] on loan until the end of the 2012\u20132013 season on 15 February 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2013/february/15/kasamis-luzern-loan|title=Kasami's Luzern Loan|publisher=Fulham FC|accessdate=15 February 2013}}</ref> He made his debut in the 4\u20130 away defeat to [[FC St. Gallen|St. Gallen]] on 24 February 2013. He scored his first goal for Luzern in the 4\u20133 away victory over [[Servette FC]] in the final game of the [[2012\u201313 Swiss Super League|2012\u201313 season]] on 1 June 2013. Following his loan spell with Luzern came to an end, Manager [[Martin Jol]] revealed Kasami took a fifty per cent cut of his wage to stay at the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fulham's man of moment Kasami took wage cut to play for Cottagers, says boss Jol|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2477115/Pajtim-Kasami-took-wage-cut-play-Fulham-says-Martin-Jol.html|publisher=Daily Mail|date=25 October 2013|accessdate=3 November 2013|location=London}}</ref> He scored Fulham's first goal of the [[2013\u201314 Premier League]] season in a 1\u20130 away victory against [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]. Kasami then scored his second goal of the season against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on 21 October; a dipping volley from the edge of the area, in a match that eventually ended a 4\u20131 away win to [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2470813/Crystal-Palace-1-Fulham-4-Pajtim-Kasamis-wonder-goal-sets-visitors-way-win.html|title= Crystal Palace 1 Fulham 4: Kasami and Sidwell bag a stunner apiece in rout |date=21 October 2013|work=Daily Mail|accessdate=22 October 2013|location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24516030|title= Crystal Palace 1 \u2013 4 Fulham|date=21 October 2013|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=22 October 2013}}</ref> This goal was nominated for the [[FIFA Pusk\u00e1s Award]] for the best goal of the year, the only one nominated from the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pajtim Kasami|url=https://www.fifa.com/ballon-dor/puskas-award/video=2463788/index.html|accessdate=14 November 2014|publisher=FIFA|date=12 November 2014}}</ref> A third was added with a deflected free kick in a 2\u20131 win at Norwich on 26 December 2013.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/competitions/premier-league/10537632/Norwich-City-1-Fulham-2-match-report.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | first=Derek | last=Davis | title=Norwich City 1 Fulham 2: match report | date=26 December 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Olympiacos===\n\nIt was announced on 9 July 2014 that Kasami had signed for [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] for a fee of \u20ac5 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28234127|title=Pajtim Kasami: Fulham midfielder leaves for Olympiakos|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 July 2014|accessdate=9 July 2014}}</ref> On 23 August 2014 he netted his first goal in his official debut as a player of [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] in a 3\u20131 home win against [[Niki Volos F.C.|Niki Volou]].<ref>{{cite news|title=The Legend kicks off the championship with a win!|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/en/article/39662/legend-kicks-championship-win|accessdate=24 August 2014|agency=Olympiacos.org|date=23 August 2014}}</ref> He scored again on 30 August 2014 against [[Panetolikos F.C.|Panetolikos]] in a 1\u20131 away draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=Panaitolikos \u2013 Olympiacos 1\u20131|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/en/article/40196/panaitolikos-olympiacos-1-1|accessdate=4 September 2014|agency=Olympiacos.org|date=30 August 2014}}</ref>\nOn 22 October 2014, [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiakos]] pulled off one of the surprises of the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] night when they beat [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] 1\u20130 in Piraeus with a first-half goal from Pajtim Kasami.<ref>{{cite news|title=Olympiakos shock Juventus with Pajtim Kasami\u2019s winner|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/oct/22/olympiakos-juventus-champions-league-match-report|publisher=www.theguardian.com|date=22 October 2014}}</ref> Kasami\u2019s goal came in the 36th minute after constant pressure from the home team which saw them deservedly record their second victory in the group.'' \u201cI feel great for the win and we worked hard for the three points. This gives us confidence for the remaining matches in the group,\u201d'' Kasami said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Champions League: Olympiakos\u2019 midfielder Kasami stun Juventus in 1\u20130 win|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/sports/article/champions-league-olympiakos-midfielder-kasami-stun-juventus-in-1-0-win|publisher=www.themalaymailonline.com|date=22 October 2014}}</ref> On 22 February 2015, Kasami experienced one of the most traumatic shocks in his life after the derby against [[Panathinaikos]]. ''\"It was a traumatic experience, I hope it doesn't happen to anybody else\"'', the 22-year-old Swiss said.'' \"I couldn't sleep for days. They had told me that these things happen in a derby, but they forget that I am just 22. Fortunately I had the support of my family and my agent. Mino Raiola came to Athens to help me recover.\"''<ref>{{cite news|title=A traumatic experience|url=http://www.sdna.gr/gr/news-in-english/arthro-news-in-english/25395/kasami-a-traumatic-experience/|publisher=sdna.gr|date=25 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u039a\u03b1\u03c3\u03ac\u03bc\u03b9: \"\u039a\u03b1\u03bd\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1\u03c2 \u03bd\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b7\u03bd \u03c4\u03bf \u03b6\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\"|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Olympiakos/kasami-kanenas-na-mhn-to-zhsei.3377795.html|publisher=www.sport24.gr|language=Greek|date=25 March 2015}}</ref> On 11 March 2015, Olympiakos's Portuguese coach [[V\u00edtor Pereira (football manager)|Vitor Pereira]] and Kasami were fined for their behavior after the team's [[Greek Cup]] quarter-final 1\u20130 win over [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK]]. The disciplinary committee of the Greek soccer federation fined Pereira 9,000 euros and Kasami was ordered to pay 7,000 euros for making gestures to the crowd which incited trouble.<ref>{{cite news|title=Olympiakos's Pereira, Kasami fined for stormy Greek Cup tie|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/4dcgi/_w_articles_wsite5_1_01/05/2015_549631|publisher=www.ekathimerini.com|date=11 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nAfter a successful [[2014\u201315 Superleague Greece|2014\u201315]], which ended with [[Double (association football)|double]] conquest, several reports in Italy are keep insisting that Kasami was likely to move to a [[Serie A]] club and it is believed that [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] or [[Inter Milan|Inter]] were the most favourable destination.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fiorentina set to table Kasami offer|url=http://www.sdna.gr/gr/news-in-english/arthro-news-in-english/39794/fiorentina-set-to-table-kasami-offer/|publisher=sdna.gr|date=26 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Inter, Raiola propone Kasami|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/news/inter-raiola-propone-kasami-440794|publisher=www.calciomercato.com|date=7 June 2015}}</ref> Despite a serious interest from [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] , [[Bayer Leverkusen]] and lately from [[A.S.Roma|Roma]], Kasami did not complete his transfer on the deadline day.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kasami likely to stay at Olympiakos|url=http://www.sdna.gr/news-english/article/108983/kasami-likely-stay-olympiakos|publisher=www.sdna.gr |date=1 September 2015}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the [[2015\u201316 Superleague Greece|2015\u201316 season]] in a hammering 5\u20131 win against [[PAS Giannina]].\n\nOn 2 October 2015, media source stated that [[Olympiacos]] former manager [[V\u00edtor Pereira (football manager)|Vitor Pereira]] and midfielder Kasami were prosecuted for provoking episodes in the [[Greek Cup]] semi final against [[AEK Athens]]. The Deputy Prosecutor Giorgos Lainis prosecuted Pajtim Kasami and Vitor Pereira. \u0391t the same time, the Football prosecutor former Sports Prosecutor Konstantinos Simitzglou had begun preliminary examination by calling witnesses in order to combine his case  with the prosecution. The two men were close to facing criminal responsibilities and even go to trial.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pereira- Kasami prosecuted|url=http://www.sdna.gr/news-english/article/120573/pereira-kasami-prosecuted|publisher=www.sdna.gr|date=2 October 2015}}</ref> On 9 June 2017, Pajtim Kasami, was sentenced to eight months in prison (on parole) for their behavior. The Swiss-Albanian international central midfielder were punished by the Greek Justice for offensively provoking the supporters of [[AEK]] after the end of [[2014\u201315 Greek Football Cup|2014-15 Greek Cup]] quarter final (0-1) between the two teams in the [[Olympic Stadium]] of Athens, after the lawsuit filed by the fan of home side, Christos Garifallou, and supported by their legal department.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0391\u03c0\u03cc\u03c6\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7-\u03ba\u03cc\u03bb\u03b1\u03c6\u03bf\u03c2: 8 \u03bc\u03ae\u03bd\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c6\u03c5\u03bb\u03ac\u03ba\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c3\u03b5 \u03a0\u03b5\u03c1\u03ad\u03b9\u03c1\u03b1, \u039a\u03b1\u03c3\u03ac\u03bc\u03b9! |url=http://www.sdna.gr/podosfairo/dikastikes-apofaseis/article/337852/apofasi-kolafos-8-mines-fylakisi-se-pereira-kasami |publisher=www.sdna.gr |date=9 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Nottingham Forest===\nOn 3 August 2016 Kasami became Nottingham Forest's seventh signing of the summer when he joined the reds on a twelve-month loan deal from [[Olympiacos]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Pajtim Kasami: Nottingham Forest sign Olympiacos midfielder on season-long loan|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36967599|publisher=www.bbc.com|date=3 August 2016}}</ref> On 27 August 2016, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3\u20131 home win against [[Leeds United F.C.]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Forest 3\u20131 Leeds|url=http://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/nottingham-forest-leeds-united-live-coverage-3274554.aspx|publisher=www.nottinghamforest.co.uk|date=27 August 2016}}</ref>\nAccording to English sources, Pajtim Kasami who is on loan at Nottingham Forest has expressed his wish to return to [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiakos]] in January transfer window. The Swiss midfielder is on loan at Nottingham Forest since the start of the season but he is not happy at the [[City Ground]]. The former Fulham star has failed to hit the heights that were expected of him when brought to Nottingham by French manager [[Philippe Montanier]], who has since been sacked.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0398\u03ad\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b1 \u03b3\u03c5\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u039f\u03bb\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc \u03bf \u039a\u03b1\u03c3\u03ac\u03bc\u03b9|url=http://www.sdna.gr/monimes-stiles/paraskinia/article/287364/thelei-na-gyrisei-ston-olympiako-o-kasami |publisher=www.sdna.gr |date=19 January 2017}}</ref>\nOn 14 February 2017, Kasami's half-volley gave Forest an early lead in a 3-2 away loss against [[Fulham F.C.]]\nOn 5 May 2017, Nottingham Forest announced that Kasami had returned to Olympiacos.\n\n===Sion===\nOn 31 August 2017, Kasami signed a three years contract with Swiss club [[FC Sion]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0395\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a3\u03b9\u03cc\u03bd \u03ad\u03c9\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf 2020 \u03bf \u039a\u03b1\u03c3\u03ac\u03bc\u03b9 |url=http://www.sdna.gr/podosfairo/superleague/article/369690/episimo-stin-sion-eos-2020-o-kasami  |publisher=www.sdna.gr |date=31 August 2017}}</ref>\nDuring the [[2018\u201319 Swiss Super League|2018-19 season]], Kasami, has scored eight goals and made three assists in 20 appearances for Sion and as a result became the subject of transfer interest from [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] and Turkish giants [[Fenerbahce]] as well as fellow Swiss team [[Basel FC]] that are also seriously interested in the versatile midfielder.<ref>{{cite news|title=Crystal Palace and Fenerbahce tracking ex-Fulham star Kasami |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/crystal-palace-and-fenerbahce-tracking-ex-fulham-star-kasami/f89z8c7evvgu14dxts5wiv1zj |publisher=www.goal.com |date=6 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March 2020, [[FC Sion]]'s madcap president [[Christian Constantin]] has terminated the contracts of all players without notice after they failed to agree to a 80% salary pay cut during coronavirus pandemic. Players such as Pajtim Kasami. [[Johan Djourou]] and [[Alex Song]] among others, wished to secure themselves legally with lawyers before agreeing to sign. <ref>{{cite news|title=Former Arsenal players Alex Song and Johan Djourou leave Swiss club FC Sion after refusing to take pay cut during coronavirus pandemic |url=https://talksport.com/football/684823/arsenal-alex-song-johan-djourou-swiss-sion-pay-cut-coronavirus/  |publisher=talksport.com |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nKasami was part of the [[Switzerland national under-17 football team|Swiss under-17 team]] that won the [[2009 FIFA U-17 World Cup|2009 World Cup]]. Whilst at Bellinzona, he earned a call-up to the [[Switzerland national under-21 football team|Switzerland U21 team]] along with teammates [[Alessandro Ciarrocchi]] and [[Frank Feltscher]], making his debut against [[Georgia national under-21 football team|Georgia U21]] on 30 May 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2011/matches/round=2000006/match=2000077/postmatch/lineups/index.html|title=Georgia draw keeps Switzerland waiting|date=30 May 2010|accessdate=2 February 2014|publisher=UEFA}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://old.acbellinzona.ch/it/article/963/granata-rossocrociato-u21|title= Granata rossocrociato, u21|date=30 May 2010|accessdate=2 February 2014|work=AC Bellinzona|language=Italian}}</ref> Kasami was selected to represent Switzerland in the [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|men's football tournament at the 2012 Summer Olympics]] as part of the [[Switzerland national under-23 football team|Swiss under-23 team]]. He played over 90 minutes in all three games in the tournament, but the team were knocked out, finishing in fourth position of their [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament \u2013 Group B|Group]]. He made his debut for the [[Switzerland national football team|Swiss senior team]] in a 1\u20130 win against Slovenia on 15 October 2013 and scored his first goal on 15 November 2013 in a friendly 2\u20131 defeat against South Korea. He scored his first competitive goal against [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]] to put Switzerland up 5\u20130 in an eventual 7\u20130 win.\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|23 February 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Pajtim Kasami|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=56424|work=Soccerbase|accessdate=23 January 2017}}</ref><ref name=sw/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!c